# Implementation Plan: Phase 3 - Notification Service

This plan details the design and implementation of Phase 3, which introduces the **Notification Service**. This service consumes transaction events from Kafka and dispatches notifications via three channels: **Email, SMS, and In-App notifications**. 

To satisfy the requirement that all channels must be **free**:
1. **Email**: We will use the existing **MailHog** SMTP server configured in Docker.
2. **SMS**: We will build a **Mock SMS Service** that simulates sending SMS by logging the message and persisting the status, avoiding any third-party API costs.
3. **In-App Notifications**: We will store these notifications in the database and expose a REST endpoint for the frontend application to fetch them.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Mock SMS Service**
> To keep the SMS feature completely free, it will be implemented as a simulated service that logs the SMS payload to the application console rather than calling a paid provider (like Twilio). The notification will still be tracked in the database as `SENT`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Gateway Routing**
> The `notification-service` will expose a public endpoint `/api/v1/notifications` to fetch in-app notifications. I will add routing for this in the API Gateway.

